    <div class="alpheios-lex-entry" lemma-id="n2921" body-key="α">
          <b><span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔκ-παγλος</span></b> , sup. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἐκπαγλότατος</span>: <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">terrible</span>, both
          of persons and of things; adv., <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔκπαγλον,
            ἔκπαγλα, ἐκπάγλως</span>, 
          <span class="alpheios-lex-gloss">terribly</span>, but often colloquially weakened,
          ‘exceedingly,’ <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">ἔκπαγλα φιλεῖν</span>, <i><span class="en">Il. 3.415</span></i> (cf. <span class="alpheios-lex-greek" lang="grc">αἰνά,
            αἰνῶς</span>).</div> <div class="alpheios-lex-footnotes en"> </div>
